<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/27a</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-28T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            28, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>571. For Finnish Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Presented credentials today to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName> who, expressing
                                        personal views, said America recognizes that Finland has set
                                        up a <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> government. He also
                                        assured us of America’s sympathy for Finland’s aspiration
                                        for independence. President unable to receive us pending
                                        internal disturbances in Finland. Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName> advised us to wait
                                        until authority of Finnish government firmly established
                                        whereupon audience with President would probably follow and
                                        recognition discussed. Please transmit above to Finnish
                                        government. <persName corresp="#p_RJN1">Reuter</persName>,
                                            <persName corresp="#p_IKB1">Ignatius</persName>.</p></quote></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>